  "doc_id": "59553",
  "text": "There is general agreement that the selection of frequencyand level-dependent gains for a hearing aid fitting for a child should be based on a prescription formula [CITATION_1] . This article presents a comparison of three hearing aid fitting methods that were in widespread use with both adults and children at the time this study was conducted. These methods are the two versions of DSL (DSL i/o and the updated version V, also called DSL m[i/o]) [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] and NAL-NL1 [CITATION_4] .",
